.\" Man page for simple shell
.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "User Commands" "man_1_simple_shell"

.SH NAME
hsh \- simple UNIX command interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
./hsh

.SH DESCRIPTION
hsh is a simple UNIX command line interpreter that reads commands
from standard input and executes them.

The shell operates in two modes:
- Interactive mode: displays a prompt and waits for user input.
- Non-interactive mode: reads commands from a pipe or file.

In interactive mode, the shell displays the prompt:
(good_boy$)

Each command entered is executed using fork() and execve().

The shell handles:
- Execution of programs using full path
- Commands with arguments
- Built-in commands

.SH BUILT-IN COMMANDS
exit
.br
	Exits the shell.

env
.br
	Prints the current environment variables.

.SH COMMAND EXECUTION
The shell parses user input into tokens and executes commands
using execve().

Only full path commands are supported (e.g. /bin/ls).

If a command is not found, an error message is displayed.

.SH EXAMPLES
Interactive mode:
.br 
$ ./hsh
.br 
(good_boy$) /bin/ls
.br 
file1 file2 file3
.br 
(good_boy$) exit

Non-interactive mode:
.br 
$ echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh
.br 
file1 file2 file3

Using arguments:
    (good_boy$) /bin/ls /tmp

.SH RETURN VALUE
The shell exits with the status of the last executed command.

